cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper focuses on style transfer using generative adversarial networks (GANs) and proposes a new model called adversarial gated networks (Gated-GAN) to transfer multiple styles in a single model. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision) which deals with image processing and analysis. The paper also discusses the challenges and limitations of traditional GANs, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as well. The proposed model involves the use of discriminative networks, which could also place it in the category of cs.GR (Graphics) or cs.MM (Multimedia).
